3)</ref> || contributor/developer || 2013\n|-\n| ''Razor Coast: Heart of the Razor''<ref>Thomas Knauss, Gary McBride, Richard Pett, and Owen KC Stephens. ''Razor Coast: Heart of the Razor'' ([[Necromancer Games|Frog God Games]], 2013)</ref> || developer || 2013\n|-\n| ''Razor Coast: Fire as She Bears''<ref>Lou Agresta and John Ling. ''Razor Coast: Fire as She Bears'' ([[Necromancer Games|Frog God Games]], 2013)</ref> || developer || 2013\n|-\n| ''Razor Coast: Call of the Frog God''<ref>Casey Christofferson. ''Razor Coast: Call of the Frog God'' ([[Necromancer Games|Frog God Games]], 2013)</ref> || developer || 2013\n|-\n| ''ONS6: Curse of Shadowhold''<ref>Alexandra Pitchford. ''ONS6: Curse of Shadowhold'' ([[Necromancer Games|Frog God Games]], 2013)</ref> || developer || 2013\n|-\n| ''Tome of Horrors 4''<ref>Scott Greene, et al. ''Tome of Horrors 4'' ([[Necromancer Games|Frog God Games]], 2013)</ref> ||contributor [uncredited] || 2013\n|-\n| ''LL3: Sword of Air''<ref>Bill Webb, et al. ''LL3: Sword of Air'' ([[Necromancer Games|Frog God Games]], 2014)</ref> || contributor/developer || 2014\n|-\n| ''Dunes of Desolation''<ref>Tom Knauss. ''Dunes of Desolation'' ([[Necromancer Games|Frog God Games]], 2014)</ref> || developer || 2014\n|-\n| ''LL4: Cults of the Sundered Kingdoms'' (with Patrick Lawinger, Casey Christofferson, and David Brohman) <ref>Patrick Lawinger, Casey Christofferson, David Brohman, and Greg A. Vaughan. ''LL4: Cults of the Sundered Kingdoms'' ([[Necromancer Games|Frog God Games]], 2015)</ref> || co-author/developer || 2015\n|-\n| ''Cults of the Sundered Kingdoms: Player's Guide''<ref>Anthony Pryor. ''Cults of the Sundered Kingdoms: Player\u2019s Guide'' ([[Necromancer Games|Frog God Games]], 2015)</ref> || developer || 2015\n|-\n| ''LL5: Borderland Provinces'' (with Matthew J. Finch and [[Bill Webb (game designer)|Bill Webb]]) <ref>Matthew J. Finch, [[Bill Webb (game designer)|Bill Webb]], and Greg A. Vaughan. ''LL5: Borderland Provinces'' ([[Necroman