b.archive.org/web/20050204224143/http://www.patman.org/ADD/resources/dungeons.asp|url-status=dead|title=Issues 1\u201371 (basic list)|access-date=February 4, 2005|df=mdy-all}}\n**{{cite web|url=http://www.intwischa.com/dungeon/|archive-date=August 6, 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110806115631/http://intwischa.com/dungeon/|url-status=dead|title=Issues 1\u2013150 (searchable)|access-date=January 19, 2011|df=mdy-all}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vaughan, Greg A.}}\n[[Category:American male writers]]\n[[Category:Dungeons & Dragons game designers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n\n{{rpg-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Greg A. Vaughan''' is an American writer who creates material for [[role-playing game|roleplaying game]]s.\n\n==Works==\nGreg A. Vaughan's role-playing credits for the ''[[Dungeons & Dragons]]'' role-playing game include ''[[Drow of the Underdark]]'',<ref>[[Ari Marmell]], [[Anthony Pryor]], [[Robert J. Schwalb]], and Greg A. Vaughan. ''[[Drow of the Underdark]]'' ([[Wizards of the Coast]], 2007)</ref> ''[[Scepter Tower of Spellgard]]'',<ref>[[David Noonan (game designer)|David Noonan]] and Greg A. Vaughan. ''[[Scepter Tower of Spellgard]]'' ([[Wizards of the Coast]], 2008)</ref> ''[[Anauroch: The Empire of Shade]]'',<ref>[[Thomas M. Reid]], [[Skip Williams]], and Greg A. Vaughan. ''[[Anauroch: The Empire of Shade]]'' ([[Wizards of the Coast]], 2007)</ref> and ''[[The Twilight Tomb]]''.<ref>Greg A. Vaughan. ''[[The Twilight Tomb]]'' ([[Wizards of the Coast]], 2006)</ref>\n\nHe was written several adventures for ''[[Dungeon (magazine)|Dungeon]]'' magazine and Paizo's ''[[Pathfinder Roleplaying Game|Pathfinder]]'' and ''GameMastery'' lines.  His [[Pathfinder Roleplaying Game|Pathfinder]] work includes ''[[Pathfinder (periodical)|Pathfinder Adventure Path #6: Spires of Xin-Shalast]],<ref>Greg A. Vaughan. ''Pathfinder Adventure Path #6: Spires of Xin-Shalast'' ([[Paizo Publishing]], 2008)</ref>'' and ''[[Pathfinder (periodical)|Pathfinder Adventure Path #11: Skeletons of Scarwall]]''.<ref>Greg A. Vaughan. ''Pathfinder Adventure Path #11: Skeletons of Scarwall'' ([[Paizo Publishing]], 2008)</ref>\n\n=== [[Wizards of the Coast]] ===\n===== ''[[Dungeons & Dragons]]'' Roleplaying Game =====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Title !! Year\n|-\n| ''[[The Twilight Tomb]]''<ref>Greg A. Vaughan. ''[[The Twilight Tomb]]'' ([[Wizards of the Coast]], 2006)</ref>  || 2006\n|-\n| ''[[Drow of the Underdark]]''<ref>[[Ari Marmell]], [[Anthony Pryor]], [[Robert J. Schwalb]], and Greg A. Vaughan. ''[[Drow of the Underdark]]'' ([[Wizards of the Coast]], 2007)</ref> (with [[Ari Marmell]], [[Robert J. Schwalb]], and [[Anthony Pryor]]) || 2007\n|-\n| ''[[Anauroch: The Empire of Shade]]''<ref>[[Thomas M. Reid]], [[Skip Williams]], and Greg A. Vaughan. ''[[Anauroch: The Empire of Shade]]'' ([[Wizards of the Coast]], 2007)</ref>  (with [[Thomas M. Reid]] and [[Skip Williams]]) || 2007\n|-\n| ''[[Scepter Tower of Spellgard]]''<ref>[[David Noonan (game designer)|David Noonan]] and Greg A. Vaughan. ''[[Scepter Tower of Spellgard]]'' ([[Wizards of the Coast]], 2008)</ref>  (with [[David Noonan (game designer)|David Noonan]]) || 2008\n|}\n\n===== ''[[Dungeon (magazine)|Dungeon]]'' Magazine Online (''A Dungeons & Dragons Roleplaying Game Supplement'') =====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Title !! Issue # !! Year\n|-\n| \"The Plague Tree\"<ref>Greg A. Vaughan. ''[[Dungeon (magazine)|Dungeon]]'' Magazine Online ([[Wizards of the Coast]], 2007)</ref> || 152 || 2007\n|-\n| \"The Lost Mines of Karak\"<ref>Greg A. Vaughan. ''[[Dungeon (magazine)|Dungeon]]'' Magazine Online ([[Wizards of the Coast]], 2008)</ref> (''[[Scales of War]]'' [[Adventure Path|AP]]) || 159 || 2008\n|-\n| \"The Brothers Gray\"<ref>Greg A. Vaughan. ''[[Dungeon (magazine)|Dungeon]]'' Magazine Online ([[Wizards of the Coast]], 2009)</ref> || 172 || 2009\n|}\n\